Quantum chaos
The quantum version of the billiards is readily studied in several ways. The classical Hamiltonian for the billiards, given above, is replaced by the stationary-state Schrödinger equation 
  
    
      
        H
        ψ
        
        =
        
        E
        ψ
      
    
    {\displaystyle H\psi \;=\;E\psi }
   or, more precisely,

  
    
      
        −
        
          
            
              ℏ
              
                2
              
            
            
              2
              m
            
          
        
        
          ∇
          
            2
          
        
        
          ψ
          
            n
          
        
        (
        q
        )
        =
        
          E
          
            n
          
        
        
